<div>
    <h2 class="section_heading">Principles</h2>

    <ol id="principles">
        <li>
            <h3>Clear</h3>
            <p>I aim to make it quick and easy to decide where you want to <%= link_to "Learn", :action => "index", :anchor => "classes_today" %> and <%= link_to "Dance", :action => "index", :anchor => "socials_today" %>, by providing all the information you need to make that decision up front and then passing you on to an external website which has more detail.</p>
        </li>

        <li>
            <h3>Comprehensive</h3>
            <p>I aim to cover every regular class going on in the capital and I've got my ear to the ground - seeking out social dancing opportunities you won't hear about anywhere else.</p>
        </li>

        <li>
            <h3>Independent</h3>
            <p>At the moment I'm just listing everything I can find, so there's no scope for bias towards any swing school or promoter, but I hope to expand the scope of the site in future, so I want to lay out my colours up front: obviously I have my preferences of lessons and social nights, but you should never see any of that preference on the site.</p>
        </li>

        <li>
            <h3>Up-to-Date</h3>
            <p>I'm wired into all of the mailing lists, Facebook groups and Twitter feeds, so if something gets cancelled, or something new comes up, you'll be the first to know. On other listings sites you'll still find long-dead dance events, but not here.</p>
        </li>

        <li>
            <h3>Sexy</h3>
            <p>Whatever you think of the other listings sites, you'd have a hard time arguing that they were pretty. I do my best to make sure that the site is attractive and easy to read.</p>
        </li>
  
    </ol>
</div>



